{"slideshow_credits": null, "snippet": "Mr. Grant, long a dominant voice on the airwaves, took advantage of the repeal of the Fairness Doctrine and thrived on the radio despite racist remarks.", "abstract": "Bob Grant, the right-wing talk radio host whose testy, confrontational manner made him a dominant voice during the drive-time hours in New York City for decades, dies at age 84; he thrived on the radio despite being boycotted for racist remarks, and despite a trademark habit of hanging up on his own callers.", "section_name": "N.Y. / Region", "print_page": "14", "document_type": "article", "byline": {"person": [{"firstname": "Paul", "role": "reported", "lastname": "VITELLO", "rank": 1, "organization": ""}], "original": "By PAUL VITELLO", "contributor": ""}, "web_url": "http://www.nytimes.com/2014/01/03/nyregion/bob-grant-a-pioneer-of-right-wing-talk-radio-dies-at-84.html", "lead_paragraph": "Mr. Grant, long a dominant voice on the airwaves, took advantage of the repeal of the Fairness Doctrine and thrived on the radio despite racist remarks.", "headline": {"main": "Bob Grant, a Combative Personality on New York Talk Radio, Dies at 84", "print_headline": "Bob Grant, a Combative Personality On New York Talk Radio, Dies at 84"}, "_id": "52c5fb3b38f0d82ae415dbb4", "word_count": "1420", "multimedia": [{"height": 126, "url": "images/2014/01/03/nyregion/OBIT-GRANT/OBIT-GRANT-thumbWide.jpg", "legacy": {"wideheight": "126", "wide": "images/2014/01/03/nyregion/OBIT-GRANT/OBIT-GRANT-thumbWide.jpg", "widewidth": "190"}, "subtype": "wide", "width": 190, "type": "image"}, {"height": 418, "url": "images/2014/01/03/nyregion/OBIT-GRANT/OBIT-GRANT-articleLarge.jpg", "legacy": {"xlarge": "images/2014/01/03/nyregion/OBIT-GRANT/OBIT-GRANT-articleLarge.jpg", "xlargewidth": "600", "xlargeheight": "418"}, "subtype": "xlarge", "width": 600, "type": "image"}, {"height": 75, "url": "images/2014/01/03/nyregion/OBIT-GRANT/OBIT-GRANT-thumbStandard.jpg", "legacy": {"thumbnail": "images/2014/0